    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-01T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-01T14:00:00-05:00" n="958"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d958">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115 Standard Vacuum oil Co./244:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-01T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 1, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>174. Your 398, June 1, 7 p.m.<note n="67" xml:id="d958fn67">Not printed.</note>
                    It is suggested that, in your discretion, you orally bring to the attention of
                    the Foreign Minister the substance of Chungking’s 234, June 1, 9 a.m., and that,
                    in so doing, you reread to him the pertinent portions of Chungking’s no. 438,
                    July 13, noon, 1939.<note n="68" xml:id="d958fn68">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_661">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 661</ref>.</note> (See Department’s 202,
                    July 15, 6 p.m., 1939.<note n="69" xml:id="d958fn69">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_662">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>, p. 662</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
